  "prompt": "How do gas stations make their money?",
  "response": "Gas stations make money through several revenue streams:\n\n1. Fuel sales\n- Slim profit margins on gasoline (usually around 5-10 cents per gallon)\n- Higher volume sales help generate revenue\n\n2. Convenience store sales\n- Typically high-margin products like snacks, drinks, and tobacco\n- Often more profitable than fuel sales\n- Impulse purchases contribute significantly to revenue\n\n3. Additional services\n- Car washes\n- Automotive supplies\n- Lottery tickets\n- ATM fees\n- Propane tank refills\n\n4. Food service\n- Prepared foods like hot dogs, sandwiches, and pizza\n- Coffee and beverage sales\n- High-profit margin items\n\n5. Repair and maintenance services\n- Some stations offer basic automotive services\n- Oil changes\n- Tire inflation\n- Minor repairs\n\n6. Credit card transaction fees\n- Earn small percentages from credit card processing\n\n7. Advertising and brand partnerships\n- Displaying advertisements\n- Partnerships with brands and suppliers\n\nWhile fuel sales attract customers, convenience store and additional services are often the most profitable aspects of a gas station's business model.",
